{
  "texts": [
    "Recent systematic benchmarking on cyclic peptide membrane permeability demonstrates that graph-based models such as AttentiveFP, MPNN, and DMPNN are among the top-performing approaches, clearly outperforming classical SVM and random-forest models built solely on fingerprint descriptors.",
    "[3].In this work, we take a complementary approach that combines the strengths of rich local chemistry of molecular fingerprints with sequence-aware topology.",
    "We introduce a monomer decoupled global alignment kernel (MD-GAK) for cyclic peptides.",
    "Each peptide is represented as an ordered sequence of monomer units.",
    "Our key design choice is to treat each monomer as a small molecule and encode it with a Morgan fingerprint, while explicitly retaining both the sequence order and the chirality of the monomers."
  ]
}